  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We consider the <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>N</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> -symmetric <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>ϕ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math> theory in two and three dimensions and determine the nonperturbative mass renormalization needed to obtain the <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>ϕ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math> continuum theory. The required nonperturbative information is obtained by resumming high-order perturbative series in the massive renormalization scheme, taking into account their Borel summability and the known large-order behavior of the coefficients. The results are in good agreement with those obtained in lattice calculations.</subfield>
